LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE BILL NO. 1086
BY RESOURCES AND ENVIRONMENT COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO TRESPASS; AMENDING CHAPTER 70, TITLE 18, IDAHO CODE, BY THE AD-
3 DITION OF A NEW SECTION 18-7045, IDAHO CODE, TO ESTABLISH PROVISIONS RE-
4 GARDING A VIOLATION OF LANDOWNER RULES FOR PERMISSIBLE USE; AND DECLAR-
5 ING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. That Chapter 70, Title 18, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
8 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
9 ignated as Section 18-7045, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
10 18-7045. VIOLATION OF LANDOWNER RULES FOR PERMISSIBLE USE. (1) As used
11 in this section:
12 (a) "Government entity" means the United States of America and those
13 entities provided for in section 6-902, Idaho Code.
14 (b) "Land" shall have the same meaning as provided in section 36-1604,
15 Idaho Code.
16 (c) "Notice" means actual notice or constructive notice and includes
17 posting signs at gates or road or trail entry points onto the land that
18 state "use restrictions apply" or similar wording and provide a website
19 address and phone number for contacting the government entity or owner.
20 (d) "Owner" shall have the same meaning as provided in section 36-1604,
21 Idaho Code.
22 (e) "Recreational purposes" shall have the same meaning as provided in
23 section 36-1604, Idaho Code.
24 (2) Whenever any government entity that manages or controls land, or
25 any owner of land, gives notice of and imposes closures, restrictions, regu-
26 lations, or prohibitions in relation to use of the land for recreational pur-
27 poses, any person who violates such closures, restrictions, regulations, or
28 prohibitions shall be guilty of trespass, punishable as provided in section
29 18-7008(3), Idaho Code.
30 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
31 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
32 July 1, 2025.

